comments.body:
@vrothberg I saw the Podman as an organic part of **RedHat development pipeline**, either scripting or declarative. Unfortunately, the user interaction using the keyboard will make the implementation of Jenkins agent too complex and the syntax of pipeline stage

 definition unclear. Changing configuration is hardly possible in the Unit test Before or BeforeAll section. I don't believe that DevOps team will accept such Unit test. Podman's Repository configuration, unlike tiny Docker's is  simply too big to make it a part of a Test suit,
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/54495912/115550478-943f8000-a2b2-11eb-97a4-5278f9445791.png)
